arget%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elived%20in%20Spain%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20time%20I%20was%206%20years%20old%20until%20I%20was%2014.%20My%20brothers%20and%20I%20went%20to%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Freturned-to-us-for-high-school-had-culture-shock-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einternational%20school%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fsurprising-things-about-living-in-spain-as-american-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMadrid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20followed%20a%20British%20curriculum.%20The%20K-12%20school%20had%20a%20total%20of%20300%20students%2C%20which%20meant%20my%20entire%20grade%20comprised%2022%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20family%20moved%20back%20to%20the%20US%2C%20I%20started%20my%20freshman%20year%20of%20high%20school.%20My%20school%20outside%20Atlanta%20had%20about%202%2C000%20students%20at%20the%20time%2C%20and%20I%20had%20almost%20600%20in%20my%20graduating%20class.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20many%20differences%20between%20the%20two%20school%20systems%2C%20and%20I%20have%20always%20wondered%20how%20my%20life%20might%20be%20different%20if%20my%20family%20had%20stayed%20in%20Spain%20and%20I'd%20received%20my%20full%20education%20there.%20And%20while%20that%20learning%20stagnated%20a%20bit%20in%20the%20US%2C%20high%20school%20was%20great%20social%20fun.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20had%20more%20subjects%20in%20Spain%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Spain%2C%20from%20the%20age%20of%2011%2C%20I%20took%2013%20subjects%2C%20which%20included%20three%20foreign%20languages%2C%20world%20history%2C%20the%20history%20of%20Spain%2C%20and%20three%20sciences.%20Some%20classes%20were%20only%20once%20a%20week%2C%20such%20as%20music%20and%20PE%2C%20and%20others%20I%20had%20every%20day%2C%20like%20math%20and%20languages.%20In%20a%20rapidly%20globalizing%20world%2C%20the%20importance%20of%20understanding%20history%20and%20knowing%20multiple%20languages%20was%20clear%20to%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20my%20high%20school%20in%20Georgia%2C%20I%20took%20six%20subjects%20with%20the%20same%20schedule%20each%20day.%20The%20sports%20coaches%20taught%20all%20my%20history%2C%20economics%2C%20and%20some%20math%20classes.%20In%20my%20world-history%20class%2C%20my%20teacher%20regularly%20put%20on%20movies%20such%20as%20%26quot%3BGladiator%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BBraveheart%26quot%3B%20instead%20of%20teaching.%20On%20Fridays%2C%20my%20economics%20teacher%20fed%20us%20%26quot%3BSaturday%20Night%20Live%26quot%3B%20reruns%20in%20class.%20What%20teenager%20doesn't%20love%20a%20movie%20day%20in%20class%3F%20Those%20classes%20were%20easy%20to%20coast%20through.%20But%20I%20also%20didn't%20learn%20anything%20from%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20emphasis%20in%20the%20US%20on%20extracurricular%20activities%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20began%20high%20school%2C%20besides%20the%20new-kid%20nervousness%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20reverse%20culture%20shock%2C%20I%20was%20surprised%20by%20the%20importance%20of%20extracurricular%20activities%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20athletics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20school%20had%20huge%2C%20well-funded%20sports%20teams%2C%20and%20tons%20of%20after-school%20clubs%2C%20and%20every%20Wednesday%2C%20classes%20ended%20at%2012%20p.m.%20so%20we%20could%20have%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20afternoon%20to%20focus%20on%20our%20club%20or%20sport%20of%20choice.%20There%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20pressure%20to%20take%20part%20in%20extracurricular%20clubs%20and%20sports%20because%20it%20would%20look%20good%20on%20a%20college%20application%20and%20could%20get%20you%20a%20college%20scholarship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Madrid%2C%20school%20sports%20were%20more%20for%20fun%20and%20staying%20healthy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20falling%20behind%20in%20my%20school%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Spain%2C%20I%20had%20foreign-language%20classes%20every%20day%20with%20the%20same%20teachers%20for%20years.%20French%20and%20Spanish%20were%20very%20immersive.%20My%20high%20school%20required%20students%20to%20take%20at%20least%20two%20years%20of%20a%20foreign%20language.%20Most%20kids%20took%20the%20bare%20minimum%20and%20then%20opted%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I%20didn't%20relish%20the%20homework%20I%20got%20as%20a%20middle%20schooler%20in%20Spain%2C%20I%20at%20least%20felt%20mentally%20stimulated%20and%20challenged.%20The%20school%20gave%20me%20a%20more%20well-rounded%2C%20strong%20foundation%20in%20core%20subjects%20and%20sparked%20my%20love%20of%20languages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHigh%20school%20felt%20like%20a%20joke%20by%20comparison.%20In%207th%20and%208th%20grades%2C%20I%20had%20already%20studied%20%26quot%3BMacbeth%26quot%3B%20and%20Franz%20Kafka's%20works%2C%20only%20to%20study%20the%20same%20things%20again%20as%20a%20senior%20in%20AP%20English.%20Much%20of%20what%20I%20learned%20in%20my%20chemistry%20and%20algebra%20classes%20in%20high%20school%20was%20a%20repeat%20of%208th%20grade.%20My%20senior-year%20math%20teacher%20didn't%20check%20our%20homework%20to%20see%20if%20the%20answers%20were%20correct.%20She%20just%20glanced%20over%20each%20person's%20page%20to%20see%20if%20you'd%20filled%20out%20numbers%2C%20which%20resulted%20in%20a%20lot%20of%20students%20%E2%80%94%20including%20me%20%E2%80%94%20making%20up%20answers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20in%20Spain%2C%20my%20classes%20from%20an%20early%20age%20felt%20higher%20quality%2C%20more%20challenging%2C%20and%20I%20was%20more%20engaged%20in%20learning%20from%20the%20same%20teachers%20repeatedly.%20I%20felt%20dumbed%20down%20at%20my%20high%20school%20by%20comparison%2C%20like%20I%20graduated%20with%20huge%20gaps%20in%20my%20learning%20especially%20related%20to%20history%20and%20current%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Spain%2C%20it%20felt%20like%20schools%20emphasized%20academics%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20making%20well-rounded%20humans%2C%20rather%20than%20getting%20the%20best%20test%20scores%20to%20get%20you%20into%20the%20best%20colleges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERe