n%20November%2022%2C%20with%20a%20deal%20to%20release%2050%20hostages%20over%20a%20period%20of%20four%20days%2C%20Israeli%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20reiterated%20that%20the%20war%20in%20Gaza%20will%20not%20stop%20with%20this.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20will%20continue%20the%20war%20until%20Gaza%20will%20not%20threaten%20Israel%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20What%20this%20means%20is%20that%20Gaza%20will%20continue%20to%20be%20an%20intensely%20life%20threatening%20workplace%20for%20journalists.%20Over%20the%20last%20few%20weeks%20Gaza%20has%20turned%20into%20a%20war%20front%20where%20journalists%20themselves%20have%20become%20victimised%20news-subjects%20as%20well%20as%20a%20moving%20picture%20of%20bravery%20and%20human%20resilience.%20And%2C%20in%20the%20process%2C%20a%20new%20and%20unique%20journalism%20phenomenon%20has%20also%20emerged%20from%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20the%20world%20only%20noticed%20the%20regular%20reporting%20of%20big%20media%20organisations%20like%20Al%20Jazeera%20from%20Gaza.%20Reporters%20from%20other%20international%20media%20were%20by%20and%20large%20unable%20to%20enter%20Gaza.%20It%20was%20amidst%20this%20that%20this%20new%20media%20phenomenon%20emerged.%20This%20was%20essentially%20linked%20to%20the%20new%20age%20of%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20phenomenon%20was%20the%20almost%20overnight%20transformation%20of%20Gazan%20content%20creators%E2%80%94those%20who%20celebrated%20their%20lives%20as%20social%20media%20stars%20capturing%20Gaza%E2%80%99s%20culture%2C%20food%2C%20and%20sights%E2%80%94into%20war%20reporters.%20They%20were%20not%20even%20familiar%20with%20the%20rough%20life%20of%20a%20normal%20peacetime%20reporter.%20Still%2C%20standing%20on%20the%20thin%20line%20between%20life%20and%20death%2C%20staring%20at%20near-certain%20death%20that%20would%20follow%20if%20one%20misstep%20happened%2C%20they%20began%20to%20speak%20to%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20%E2%80%9Cnew%E2%80%9D%20journalists%20as%20well%20as%20existing%20professional%20journalists%20became%20victims%20of%20the%20war%20in%20Gaza.%20We%20cannot%20see%20them%20separately.%20Both%20conventional%20journalists%20as%20well%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9Cnew%20ones%E2%80%9D%20showed%20and%20continue%20to%20show%20extraordinary%20courage%2C%20commitment%20and%20endurance%20in%20the%20face%20of%20unprecedented%20human%20tragedies.%20Some%20of%20them%20may%20have%20biases.%20But%20their%20significance%20and%20courage%20cannot%20be%20underestimated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%20of%20writing%20this%2C%20reports%20say%2053%20of%20the%20journalists%20and%20media%20workers%20reporting%20from%20Gaza%20and%20Israel%20have%20been%20killed%20in%20the%20war.%20The%20Committee%20to%20Protect%20Journalists%20(CPJ)%2C%20a%20New%20York-based%20NGO%2C%20says%2046%20Palestinian%20journalists%2C%204%20Israeli%20journalists%20and%203%20Lebanese%20journalists%20were%20killed.%20The%20group%20said%20four%20Israeli%20journalists%20were%20killed%20in%20a%20Hamas%20attack%20on%20October%207%2C%20and%203%20Lebanese%20journalists%20were%20killed%20on%20the%20Israel-Lebanon%20border.%20Apart%20from%20this%2C%203%20journalists%20are%20missing%2C%2011%20journalists%20injured%20and%2018%20arrested.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fpalestine-gaza-israel-journalist-media%5C%22%3EMore%20Than%20One%20Journalist%20Per%20Day%20Is%20Dying%20in%20the%20Israel-Gaza%20Conflict.%20This%20Has%20to%20Stop%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithout%20the%20social%20media%20content%20creators-turned%20war%20reporters%20in%20Gaza%2C%20the%20world%20would%20never%20have%20understood%20the%20horrors%20of%20this%20war.%20It%20is%20indeed%20a%20breathtaking%20experience%20as%20you%20see%20these%20content%20creators%20jumping%20into%20the%20flames%20of%20war%20in%20the%20historical%20social%20and%20geographical%20background%20of%20the%20wondrously%20beautiful%20locales%20of%20Middle%20East%20Asia.%20The%20region%20has%20often%20been%20described%20as%20the%20cradle%20of%20human%20civilisation.%20This%20combined%20with%20the%20rich%20hues%20of%20the%20unique%20culture%20of%20the%20persecuted%20and%20hunted%20people%20called%20Palestinians%20make%20this%20media%20experience%20truly%20heroic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20brave%20media%20warriors%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%20us%20look%20a%20little%20closely%20at%20some%20of%20these%20brave%20media%20warriors.%20For%20instance%2C%20there%20is%2025-year-old%20Bizan%20Awda%2C%20who%20viewers%20used%20to%20see%20as%20a%20smiling%20girl%20at%20a%20women%E2%80%99s%20boxing%20training%20facility%20in%20Gaza%2C%20wearing%20boxing%20gloves%20on%20her%20hands%2C%20and%20stating%20that%20the%20sport%20is%20unfamiliar%20to%20Gazan%20women%2C%20but%20they%20must%20come%20and%20try%20it.%20This%20%E2%80%9Cboxing%20coach%20video%E2%80%9D%20is%20an%20old%20story%20now.%20Bizan%20is%20now%20known%20as%20the%20journalist%20who%20broke%20down%20into%20tears%20while%20reporting%20that%20she%20was%20at%20the%20entrance%20of%20a%20hospital%20in%20Gaza%20just%20two%20seconds%20before%20a%20bomb%20fell%20and%20many%20people%20died.%20In%20the%20early%20days%20of%20the%20war%2C%20Bizan%20could%20be%20seen%20jovially%20interacting%20with%20the%20small%20children%20who%20were%20cleaning%20the%20premises%20of%20Al%20Shifa%20Hospital%2C%20helping%20others%20however%20they%20could%2C%20trying%20to%20make%20them%20laugh.%20The%20laughter%20has%20stopped%20now.%20The%20girl%E2%80%99s%20face%20now%20is%20permanently%20shadowed%20by%20fear%20and%20excruciating%20pain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMahmoud%20Suwaitar%20is%20a%20comedian%20from%20Gaza.%20One%20of%20the%20founders%20of%20Tashweesh%2C%20a%20comedy%20troupe%20in%20Gaza.%20Before%20the%20war%2C%20he%20had%20600%2C000%20Instagram%20followers.%20Now%20Mahmood%20Suwaitar%20is%20reporting%20the%20war.%20With%20980%2C000%20followers%20on%20Instagram%2C%20Ahmed%20Hijazi%20had%20become%20a%20social%20media%20star%20capturing%20the%20culture%20and%20beauty%20of%20Gaza.%20Al%20Jazeera%20reported%20that%20Hijazi%E2%80%99s%20wife%20had%20a%20photo%20studio%20in%20the%20Gaza%20Tower%2C%20which%20was%20bombed%20by%20Israel%20in%20the%20early%20days%20of%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPlastia%20Alaqat%20is%20another%2020-year-old%20Gazan%20vlogger.%20Plastia%20used%20to%20make%20videos%20that%20focused%20on%20women%E2%80%99s%20education.%20Since%20the%20war%20began%2C%20this%20vlogger%20has%20given%20an%20incredibly%20honest%20account%20of%20how%20the%20war%20affects%20her%20on%20an%20everyday%20basis.%20Ali%20Nisman%20was%20a%20Palestinian%20actor%2C%20social%20activist%20and%20content%20creator%20killed%20in%20an%20Israeli%20bombing%20on%20October%2013.%20Even%20a%20few%20hours%20before%20that%2C%20Nisman%20had%20uploaded%20a%20video%20on%20his%20Instagram%20page%20reporting%20on%20the%20suffering%20of%20the%20people%20of%20Gaza.%20Nisman%E2%80%99s%20roles%20in%20the%202022%20film%20%E2%80%98Nasr%20Gilboa%20Street%E2%80%99%20and%20the%20television%20series%20%E2%80%98Sky%20Gate%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98Al%20Rooh%E2%80%99%20had%20won%20great%20acclaim%20from%20the%20film%20buffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F17091305%2FScreenshot-2023-11-17-at-9.12.38%25E2%2580%25AFAM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F17091305%2FScreenshot-2023-11-17-at-9.12.38%25E2%2580%25AFAM.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F17091305%2FScreenshot-2023-11-17-at-9.12.38%25E2%2580%25AFAM-300x185.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F17091305%2FScreenshot-2023-11-17-at-9.12.38%25E2%2580%25AFAM-1024x632.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-685141%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22741%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Sheikh%20Redwan%20neighbourhood%20of%20Gaza%20city%2C%20October%208%2C%202023.%3Cbr%3EPhoto%3A%20Bashar%20Taleb%2FUN%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20world%20saw%20Al%20Jazeera%E2%80%99s%20reporter%20Yumna%20El%20Sayed%20reporting%20live%20the%20Israeli%20bombardment%20of%20a%20Gaza%20Tower%20just%20behind%20her.%20One%20heard%20the%20heartrending%20cry%20that%20came%20out%20of%20Yumna%20at%20that%20time%20as%20well%20as%20her%20shock%20as%20she%20became%20breathless%20seeing%20the%20horrific%20scene.%20This%20was%20one%20of%20the%20first%20frightening%20journalist%20pictures%20that%20came%20out%20during%20this%20war.%20Yumna%20is%20a%20journalist%20who%20appeared%20to%20be%20in%20her%20early%20thirties.%20But%20look%20at%20her%20now%2C%20more%20than%20a%20month%20into%20the%20war.%20She%20looks%20like%20a%2050%20or%2060-year-old%20woman.%20Yumna%E2%80%99s%20face%20bears%20the%20scars%20of%20reporting%20from%20the%20hellhole%20of%20human%20tragedy%2C%20living%20in%20a%20sort%20of%20hell%20herself%2C%20fleeing%20northern%20Gaza%20to%20the%20south%2C%20and%20filming%20herself%20comforting%20her%20own%20children%20as%20fire%20bombs%20rained%20down%20around%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFour%20children%20of%20Muhammad%20al-Aloul%2C%20a%20photographer%20of%20the%20Turkish%20news%20agency%20Anadolu%20were%20killed%20in%20an%20airstrike.%20Salman%20al-Bashir%2C%20a%20journalist%20on%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority%E2%80%99s%20TV%20channel%2C%20was%20reporting%20live%20when%20the%20news%20of%20his%20colleague%20Muhammad%20Abu%20Hattab%E2%80%99s%20death%20came.%20Salman%20al-Bashir%20tearfully%20removed%20his%20press%20jacket%2C%20which%20is%20worn%20by%20journalists%2C%20saying%20that%20journalists%20are%20not%20at%20all%20protected%20on%20this%20battlefield.%20The%20whole%20world%20saw%20the%20presenter%20who%20was%20sitting%20and%20talking%20with%20him%20in%20the%20studio%20also%20breaking%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmidst%20all%20this%2C%20Israel%20has%20informed%20the%20international%20media%20that%20it%20cannot%20guarantee%20the%20safety%20of%20journalists%20working%20in%20Gaza.%20Many%20journalists%E2%80%99%20family%20members%20were%20killed%20in%20Israeli%20bombings.%20Before%20the%20war%20started%2C%20Motaz%20Azaizah%20was%20a%2024-year-old%20photojournalist%2C%20Instagram%20influencer%2C%20and%20chronicler%20of%20daily%20life%20in%20Gaza%20and%20Israeli%20oppression.%20After%20the%20war%20started%2C%20all%20his%20attention%20was%20towards%20reporting%20deaths%20and%20devastation%20in%20Gaza.%20Azaiza%20went%20through%20the%20tragedy%20of%20filming%20the%20death%20of%20his%2015%20family%20members%20who%20were%20killed%20in%20the%20bombing%20of%20the%20Deir%20al-Bala%20refugee%20camp%20in%20Gaza.%20Videos%20of%20Azaiza%20and%20another%20journalist%2C%20Hind%20Khoudary%2C%20are%20now%20rarely%20seen.%20Both%20of%20them%20confirmed%20in%20a%20video%20aired%20a%20few%20days%20ago%20that%20they%20are%20alive%2C%20but%20they%20are%20trying%20to%20find%20their%20estranged%20family%20members%2C%20according%20to%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20journalist%20was%20seen%20rushing%20to%20the%20hospital%20in%20a%20car%20with%20two%20seriously%20injured%20toddlers%20on%20his%20lap.%20He%20was%20shouting%20to%20the%20camera%20that%20he%20just%20grabbed%20two%20wounded%20kids%20from%20among%20the%20many%20injured%20in%20the%20bombing%20and%20was%20going%20to%20the%20hospital%20with%20them.%20The%20children%E2%80%99s%20faces%20were%20covered%20in%20blood.%20The%20three%20brothers%20and%20father%20of%20Turkish%20news%20agency%20Anadolu%E2%80%99s%20photographer%20Ali%20Jadallah%20were%20killed%20in%20an%20Israeli%20airstrike.%20Ali%20himself%20released%20a%20picture%20of%20him%20driving%20to%20bury%20his%20father%E2%80%99s%20body%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2F687639%2Fisrael-palestine-war-benjamin-netanyahu-captain-america-problem%2F%5C%22%3EIsrael-Palestine%20War%3A%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%E2%80%99s%20Captain%20America%20problem%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20journalism%20classes%20around%20the%20world%20teach%20that%20objectivity%20is%20the%20cornerstone%20of%20a%20journalist%E2%80%99s%20profession.%20Journalists%20in%20Gaza%20are%20going%20through%20a%20situation%20where%20they%20themselves%20turn%20into%20victims%2C%20subject%20to%20extreme%20kinds%20of%20pain%20and%20human%20tragedy%2C%20enduring%20death%20and%20separation.%20The%20cumulative%20impact%20of%20all%20this%20is%20that%20they%20themselves%20become%20news%20stories%20and%20objective%20reality%20of%20the%20world%20thus%20making%20them%20subjects%20of%20headlines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAl%20Jazeera%20Arabic%20Channel%E2%80%99s%20Gaza%20Bureau%20Chief%2C%20Wael%20Dahdo%2C%20lost%20his%20wife%2C%2015-year-old%20son%2C%207-year-old%20daughter%20and%20grandchild%20in%20the%20bombing.%20A%20colleague%2C%20Yumna%20El%20Said%2C%20who%20fled%20to%20southern%20Gaza%2C%20told%20Al%20Jazeera%20that%20Dahdo%20remained%20in%20Gaza%20saying%20%E2%80%9CI%20cannot%20leave%20the%20Gazans.%E2%80%9D%20These%20words%2C%20spoken%20by%20a%20veteran%20journalist%20like%20Dahdo%2C%20show%20how%20complicated%20the%20situation%20in%20Gaza%20is.%20The%20question%20arises%20whether%20a%20journalist%20can%20leave%20the%20place%20where%20he%20is%20assigned%2C%20and%20flee.%20In%20all%20probability%2C%20the%20journalist%20must%20have%20wondered%20who%20would%20tell%20the%20world%20the%20life%20stories%20of%20people%20who%20resolutely%20decided%20to%20stay%20put%20in%20Gaza%2C%20if%20he%20chose%20the%20option%20of%20running%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDahdo%20returned%20to%20war%20reporting%20the%20very%20next%20day%20after%20his%20entire%20family%20was%20killed.%20One%20cannot%20but%20wonder%20why%20Al%20Jazeera%20reassigned%20him%20to%20reporting%20instead%20of%20leaving%20him%20to%20mourn%20alone.%20But%20the%20violence%20in%20Gaza%20continues.%20If%20not%20Dahdo%2C%20who%20will%20give%20the%20news%3F%20Perhaps%2C%20in%20the%20face%20of%20the%20tragedy%20of%20his%20people%2C%20Dahdo%20is%20not%20ready%20to%20weep%20until%20this%20war%20is%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20the%20multifaceted%20images%20of%20bravery%20and%20media%20commitment%20are%20presented%20to%20the%20world%2C%20there%20are%20some%20important%20questions%20in%20the%20debate%20about%20journalism%20emerging%20from%20the%20Gaza%20war.%20Many%20layers%20of%20wartime%20journalism%2C%20including%20some%20unsavoury%20facets%2C%20can%20be%20deduced%20in%20those%20discussions.%20Still%2C%20amidst%20all%20these%20layers%2C%20what%20stands%20out%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20journalists%20of%20Gaza%2C%20from%20the%20content%20creators%20who%20had%20to%20become%20journalists%20on%20the%20war%20front%2C%20are%20truly%20worth%20a%20big%20salute.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMedia%20action%3A%20questions%20raised%20by%20the%20Hamas-Israel%20war%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20among%20the%20troubling%20questions%20is%20the%20one%20related%20to%20the%20coverage%20of%20happenings%20on%20October%207%2C%20the%20day%20of%20mass%20murder.%20There%20were%20some%20journalists%20with%20Hamas%20who%20went%20along%20with%20the%20forces%20into%20Israel%20that%20day%20.%20Hamas%20attacked%20and%20killed%20soldiers%20and%20civilians%20alike.%20These%20were%20journalists%20from%20Gaza.%20But%20they%20were%20also%20freelancers%20reporting%20to%20the%20international%20media.%20Especially%20four%20of%20them.%20The%20four%20provided%20coverage%20of%20the%20Hamas%20attack%20to%20international%20news%20organisations%20such%20as%20the%20New%20York%20Times%2C%20Reuters%2C%20CNN%20and%20the%20Associated%20Press.%20These%20media%20houses%20published%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20journalists%20can%20be%20seen%20in%20videos%20of%20Hamas%20violence.%20This%20was%20first%20pointed%20out%20by%20Honest%20Reporting%2C%20a%20pro-Israel%20organization%20whose%20stated%20aim%20is%20to%20expose%20anti-Semitism%20in%20the%20media.%20They%20brought%20this%20presence%20of%20embedded%20journalists%20along%20with%20Hamas%20to%20public%20attention%20through%20an%20article%20published%20on%20their%20website%2C%20%E2%80%9CBroken%20Borders%3A%20AP%20%26amp%3B%20Reuters%20Pictures%20of%20Hamas%20Atrocities%20Raise%20Ethical%20Questions%E2%80%99%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27090342%2Fimage1170x530cropped-6.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221170%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27090342%2Fimage1170x530cropped-6.jpg%201170w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27090342%2Fimage1170x530cropped-6-300x136.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27090342%2Fimage1170x530cropped-6-1024x464.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686477%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22530%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20five-year-old%20boy%20drinks%20bottled%20water%20delivered%20by%20UNICEF%20in%20the%20Khan%20Younis%20camp%20in%20Gaza.%20Photo%3A%20UNICEF%2FEyad%20El%20Baba%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDid%20these%20journalists%20go%20along%20knowing%20that%20such%20widespread%20violence%20was%20going%20to%20happen%3F%20If%20so%2C%20did%20they%20inform%20the%20concerned%20authorities%20in%20the%20media%20outlets%20that%20employ%20them%2C%20such%20as%20the%20%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20Reuters%3F%20And%20if%20these%20international%20media%20organisations%20had%20known%20this%2C%20are%20they%20not%20complicit%20in%20such%20a%20massacre%3F%20Moreover%2C%20Honest%20Reporting%20released%20another%20photo.%20It%20was%20a%20picture%20of%20Yahya%20Sinwar%2C%20the%20head%20of%20Hamas%20in%20Gaza%2C%20kissing%20one%20of%20the%20four%20journalists%20on%20his%20cheek.%20This%20picture%20was%20of%20Hassan%20Eslaiya%2C%20a%20freelance%20journalist%20in%20Gaza%20who%20provided%20CNN%20with%20news%20and%20pictures%20of%20the%20violence.%20A%20video%20also%20surfaced%20of%20Hassan%20Eslaiya%20riding%20a%20motorcycle%20with%20a%20man%20sitting%20on%20the%20back%20with%20a%20grenade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJournalism%20turning%20complex%20and%20confusing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20this%20disclosure%20by%20Honest%20Reporting%2C%20the%20Israeli%20Minister%20of%20Information%20and%20Communications%20issued%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20four%20international%20media%20organisations%20involved%3A%20%3Cem%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Reuters%2C%20CNN%20and%20the%20Associated%20Press.%20The%20letter%20addressed%20the%20questions%20raised%20above.%20The%20Israeli%20side%20has%20alleged%20that%20these%20freelance%20journalists%20identify%20with%20the%20cause%20and%20actions%20of%20Hamas%20who%20committed%20the%20violence.%20To%20prove%20this%2C%20the%20letter%20pointed%20out%20the%20particular%20style%20of%20reporting%20of%20one%20of%20the%20reporters%20when%20the%20incident%20took%20place.%20Subsequently%2C%20all%20the%20four%20media%20houses%20issued%20a%20statement%20saying%20that%20they%20were%20not%20aware%20of%20the%20scale%20and%20nature%20of%20the%20violence.%20Reuters%20explained%20that%20on%20October%207%2C%20the%20day%20of%20the%20attack%2C%20they%20only%20bought%20photos%20from%20two%20Gazan%20freelance%20journalists%20who%20were%20on%20the%20Gaza-Israel%20border%2C%20and%20with%20whom%20they%20had%20no%20previous%20relationship.%20Moreover%2C%20if%20you%20look%20at%20the%20time%20these%20photos%20were%20taken%2C%20it%20is%20clear%20that%20they%20were%20taken%2045%20minutes%20after%20Israel%20officially%20announced%20the%20arrival%20of%20the%20attackers%2C%20Reuters%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Associated%20Press%20and%20CNN%20described%20the%20incident%20as%20simply%20gathering%20information%20from%20available%20sources%2C%20such%20as%20freelancers%2C%20as%20is%20often%20done%20in%20a%20sudden%20incident.%20And%20they%20said%20they%20had%20severed%20all%20ties%20with%20Hassan%20Eslaiya%2C%20the%20freelance%20journalist%20in%20Gaza.%20%3Cem%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20said%20%E2%80%93%20There%20is%20no%20evidence%20to%20make%20an%20allegation%20about%20our%20Gaza%20freelancer.%20This%20allegation%20is%20false%20and%20objectionable.%20It%E2%80%99s%20an%20accusation%20that%20could%20unnecessarily%20endanger%20journalists%20in%20Israel%20and%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20politics%20of%20media%20work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20summary%20of%20the%20problem%20discussed%20above%20has%20to%20factor%20in%20the%20fact%20that%20Hamas%20is%20both%20a%20political%20movement%20and%20an%20armed%20militant%20group%20that%20has%20openly%20adopted%20terrorist%20attacks%20as%20its%20modus%20operandi.%20This%20complexity%20makes%20media%20coverage%20of%20Hamas%20extremely%20difficult.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20question%20is%20how%20%E2%80%98neutral%E2%80%99%20media%20work%20can%20be%2C%20emerging%20from%20a%20people%20who%20have%20been%20occupied%20and%20oppressed%20by%20Israel%20for%20many%20decades.%20The%20second%20aspect%20is%20that%20in%20the%20age%20of%20social%20media%2C%20where%20everyone%20is%20a%20citizen%20journalist%20and%20content%20creator%2C%20the%20boundaries%20between%20who%20is%20an%20ordinary%20citizen%20and%20who%20is%20a%20journalist%20are%20disappearing.%20The%20third%20question%20is%20this%20%E2%80%93%20a%20journalist%20gets%20information%20that%20such%20an%20act%20of%20violence%20is%20going%20to%20take%20place.%20Still%2C%20in%20all%20probability%2C%20those%20journalists%20were%20not%20fully%20aware%20of%20the%20horrific%20nature%20of%20the%20forthcoming%20violence.%20In%20such%20cases%2C%20journalists%20only%20get%20rumours%20first%20that%20something%20is%20going%20to%20happen.%20It%20is%20the%20natural%20instinct%20of%20the%20reporter%20to%20go%20after%20these%20bits%20and%20pieces%20of%20information%20or%20rumours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2F686449%2Fpalestine-tiktok-territory-rights%2F%5C%22%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20More%20Than%20Just%20TikTok%3A%20How%20the%20Talk%20on%20Palestine%20Shifted%20from%20Territory%20to%20Rights%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20when%20the%20true%20nature%20of%20the%20violence%20is%20understood%20at%20some%20point%2C%20what%20steps%20can%20those%20journalists%20take%3F%20Is%20the%20primary%20mission%20to%20report%20the%20news%2C%20or%20to%20inform%20those%20concerned%2C%20to%20prevent%20violence%3F%20While%20reading%20history%2C%20we%20have%20seen%20instances%20of%20reporting%20where%20the%20stakeholders%20are%20informed%20by%20journalists%20in%20similar%20circumstances%20and%20the%20news%20is%20also%20reported.%20Sometimes%20we%20have%20also%20seen%20situations%20where%20both%20of%20these%20cannot%20be%20done.%20Moreover%2C%20reporting%20an%20event%20has%20extreme%20importance.%20If%20the%20violence%20is%20documented%2C%20it%20may%20even%20help%20identify%20the%20perpetrator%20later.%20Capturing%20what%20happened%20is%20important%20at%20several%20levels.%20Whether%20it%20is%20in%20Israel%20or%20Gaza%2C%20what%20involves%20journalists%20risking%20their%20lives%20to%20report%20a%20mass%20murder%20is%20also%20about%20justice%20for%20those%20dead%20people.%20If%20it%20is%20to%20be%20proven%20in%20later%20investigations%20what%20crimes%20have%20been%20committed%2C%20if%20both%20sides%20want%20justice%2C%20there%20needs%20to%20be%20rock%20solid%20evidence%2C%20and%20that%20is%20where%20the%20documentation%20as%20carried%20out%20by%20journalists%20becomes%20extremely%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEfforts%20to%20fact%20check%20and%20challenges%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20problems%20faced%20by%20international%20media%20reporting%20the%20war%20from%20outside%20without%20being%20able%20to%20go%20inside%20Gaza%20are%20many.%20Relying%20on%20freelancers%20in%20Gaza%20or%20the%20official%20Israeli%20military%20for%20news%20poses%20major%20challenges%20to%20factual%20reporting.%20On%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20while%20freelancers%E2%80%99%20reports%20from%20Gaza%20are%20invaluable%20documentation%2C%20they%20come%20with%20no%20other%20means%20of%20verifying%20the%20accuracy%20of%20the%20information%20they%20provide.%20The%20same%20problem%20exists%20with%20the%20information%20provided%20by%20the%20Israeli%20forces.%20Many%20content%20creators%20in%20Gaza%20have%20complained%20that%20their%20posts%20have%20been%20%E2%80%98shadow%20banned%E2%80%99%20by%20social%20media.%20There%20could%20be%20many%20factors%20behind%20such%20censorship%20by%20social%20media%20companies.%20These%20could%20include%20the%20need%20to%20censor%20picturisations%20of%20extreme%20violence%2C%20the%20depiction%20of%20close-ups%20of%20gruesome%20injuries%20and%20calls%20for%20violence.%20It%20can%20also%20be%20assumed%20that%20political%20messages%20against%20the%20politically%20mighty%20countries%20such%20as%20Israel%20and%20the%20United%20States%2C%20or%20messages%20that%20undermine%20the%20supremacy%20of%20the%20Western%20narrative%2C%20are%20also%20suppressed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20media%20persons%2C%20content%20creators%2C%20and%20the%20ordinary%20people%20who%20are%20turned%20by%20war%20into%20conflict%20journalists%20believe%20they%20have%20a%20responsibility%20to%20speak%20the%20truth%20about%20Gaza%20to%20the%20world.%20Unfiltered%2C%20raw%20and%20authentic%20are%20the%20terminology%20by%20which%20the%20world%20generally%20describes%20the%20images%20and%20information%20provided%20by%20content%20creators%20in%20Gaza.%20The%20methods%20of%20fact-checking%20and%20scrutiny%20of%20potential%20errors%20at%20many%20editorial%20levels%20that%20are%20done%20in%20normal%2C%20curated%20journalism%20are%20well-nigh%20impossible%20in%20this%20war.%20Ghastly%20spectacles%20of%20horrific%20mass%20killings%20reach%20the%20audience%20uncut%20and%20unfiltered.%20The%20brutal%20honesty%20of%20these%20images%20is%20hard-hitting.%20Recognizing%20its%20implications%20to%20approved%20journalism%20practices%2C%20the%20mainstream%20media%20generally%20follow%20the%20pattern%20of%20masking%20the%20most%20horrific%20and%20tragic%20scenes%2C%20even%20in%20this%20war.%20But%20on%20social%20media%2C%20those%20scenes%20often%20come%20out%20without%20such%20precautions.%20The%20formal%20and%20informal%20consensus%20in%20journalism%20is%20that%20badly%20injured%20and%20mutilated%20corpses%20must%20not%20be%20shown%20as%20it%20is%20a%20violation%20of%20the%20sanctity%20and%20dignity%20of%20human%20life.%20When%20there%20is%20a%20relentless%20massacre%20that%20continuously%20diminishes%20the%20value%20of%20human%20life%2C%20to%20argue%20for%20such%20restraint%20also%20becomes%20ridiculous%20and%20meaningless.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F12125115%2Fimage1170x530cropped-4.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221170%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F12125115%2Fimage1170x530cropped-4.jpg%201170w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F12125115%2Fimage1170x530cropped-4-300x136.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F12125115%2Fimage1170x530cropped-4-1024x464.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-684525%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22530%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAl%20Shifa%20hospital%20is%20being%20used%20as%20shelter%20for%20displaced%20families%20in%20Gaza.%20Photo%3A%20WHO%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20did%20Gaza%20come%20out%20on%20pop%20in%20the%20media%20war%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEveryone%20now%20realises%20that%20there%20is%20a%20deadly%20war%20going%20on%20in%20Gaza%20as%20well%20as%20a%20media%20war.%20No%20one%20thinks%20that%20Gaza%20will%20fight%20and%20win%20a%20war%20waged%20against%20Israel%2C%20a%20deadly%20armed%20power%2C%20backed%20by%20an%20even%20greater%20force%2C%20the%20United%20States.%20But%20Gaza%20is%20far%20ahead%20in%20the%20media%20war.%20For%20that%2C%20we%20have%20to%20thank%20the%20aforementioned%20journalists%2C%20content%20creators%2C%20and%20ordinary%20people%20who%20have%20become%20war%20reporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlmost%2025%20years%20ago%2C%20when%20this%20writer%20was%20working%20at%20the%20international%20desk%20of%20Asianet%20News%2C%20a%20Malayalam%20regional%20language%20channel%2C%20and%20preparing%20content%20for%20bulletins%2C%20then%20too%20the%20Israeli-Palestinian%20conflict%20was%20a%20major%20and%20live%20topic.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20the%20Palestinians%20were%20mostly%20an%20unarmed%20population%20that%20picked%20up%20stones%20and%20threw%20them%20at%20Israeli%20forces.%20It%20was%20visibly%20so%20in%20the%20footage%20that%20was%20coming%20from%20there.%20And%20their%20voices%20were%20not%20legible%20at%20all.%20When%20they%20spoke%2C%20it%20was%20in%20Arabic%2C%20in%20a%20language%20unknown%20to%20the%20outside%20world%2C%20especially%20the%20western%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20we%20say%20that%20social%20media%20has%20fostered%20a%20new%20breed%20of%20journalists%20in%20Gaza%2C%20there%20is%20another%20important%20thing%20that%20we%20need%20to%20understand%20and%20assimilate.%20Today%20those%20popular%20journalists%2Fcontent%20creators%20all%20speak%20good%20English%20to%20the%20world.%20The%20schools%20started%20in%20Gaza%20by%20UNRWA%20(United%20Nations%20Relief%20and%20Works%20Agency%20for%20Palestine%20Refugees%20in%20the%20Near%20East)%20and%20the%20education%20provided%20there%2C%20including%20English%2C%20have%20created%20a%20new%20generation%20of%20educated%20people%20in%20Gaza.%20This%20is%20also%20why%20Israel%20can%20be%20defeated%20in%20the%20media%20war%20even%20when%20Gaza%20is%20losing%20the%20war%20of%20arms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2F684798%2Funited-states-israel-palestine%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20US%20Is%20Part%20of%20the%20Problem%20in%20Israel-Palestine%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael%20even%20accused%20UNRWA%20schools%20in%20Palestine%20run%20by%20the%20United%20Nations%20as%20centres%20providing%20terrorist%20training.%20These%20allegations%20have%20been%20dismissed%20by%20the%20world%2C%20as%20a%20whole%2C%20with%20the%20contempt%20they%20deserve.%20But%20it%20is%20clear%20that%20UNRWA%20schools%20have%20played%20a%20role%20in%20empowering%20Gazans%2C%20especially%20the%20girls%20and%20women%20of%20Gaza.%20They%20got%20a%20new%20language%20to%20express%20their%20views%20to%20the%20world.%20They%20gained%20the%20confidence%20to%20do%20so%20through%20education.%20Interviews%20of%20many%20Gazans%20living%20outside%20Gaza%20%E2%80%93%20most%20of%20them%20professionals%2C%20academics%2C%20etc.%20%E2%80%93%20have%20already%20appeared%20on%20several%20TV%20channels.%20They%20articulate%20the%20politics%20of%20Gaza%E2%80%99s%20resistance%20to%20the%20world%20in%20English%2C%20with%20great%20erudition%20and%20ease.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20lesson%20for%20all%20oppressed%20people%20in%20the%20world%20who%20are%20looking%20for%20a%20path%20of%20resistance.%20It%20proves%20that%20an%20armed%20struggle%20is%20only%20a%20temporary%20solution.%20The%20power%20of%20knowledge%20will%20win%20the%20long%20battle%2C%20howsoever%20slow%20it%20is.%20The%20experience%20of%20journalists%20and%20content%20creators%20in%20Gaza%20continues%20to%20underscore%20that%20the%20English%20language%20is%20the%20best%20weapon%20to%20break%20the%20monopoly%20in%20the%20information%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheaidem.com%2Fen-how-conflict-in-gaza-changed-the-nature-of-journalism-and-reporting%2F%5C%22%3Eoriginally%20published%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheaidem.com%2F%5C%22%3Ethe%20AIDEM%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701780327000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F19092706%2FF8t8SUEWMAAvoa0.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fhow-the-war-in-palestine-is-being-broadcasted-amid-israels-growing-attacks-on-journalists%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Without%20the%20social%20media%20content%20creators-turned%20war%20reporters%20in%20Gaza%2C%20the%20world%20would%20never%20have%20understood%20the%20horrors%20of%20this%20war.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fhow-the-war-in-palestine-is-being-broadcasted-amid-israels-growing-attacks-on-journalists%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Pak-based%20terrorist%20Lakhbir%20Rode%E2%80%99s%20close%20aide%20Paramjit%20Singh%20arrested%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701780206000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105758997%2Cimgsize-855812.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Famritsar%2Fpak-based-terrorist-lakhbir-rodes-close-aide-paramjit-singh-arrested-at-amritsar-airport%2Farticleshow%2F105759003.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Giving%20details%2C%20Director%20General%20of%20Police%20(DGP)%20Punjab%20Gaurav%20Yadav%20informed%20on%20Tuesday%20that%20Paramjit%2C%20a%20British%20citizen%20and%20a%20founder%20member%20of%20the%20International%20Sikh%20Youth%20Federation%20(ISYF)%2C%20was%20allegedly%20involved%20in%20terror%20activities%20in%20Punjab%20in%20the%20early%2090s%20and%20was%20later%20arrested%20in%202003.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22YUDHVIR%20RANA%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Famritsar%2Fpak-based-terrorist-lakhbir-rodes-close-aide-paramjit-singh-arrested-at-amritsar-airport%2Farticleshow%2F105759003.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Talking%20to%20my%20friends%20every%20day%20made%20me%20realize%20I%20don't%20need%20marriage%20or%20kids%20to%20be%20happy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Woman%20holding%20iphone%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655b79579c7d23cb3b9d5981%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222001%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ETim%20Robberts%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20video-messaging%20app%20Marco%20Polo%20gave%20me%20an%20inside%20look%20at%20marriage%20and%20motherhood.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMy%20friends'%20real%20talk%20helped%20me%20figure%20out%20that%20marriage%20and%20kids%20aren't%20a%20priority%20for%20me.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOur%20friendships%20work%20because%20we%20care%20about%20the%20details%20of%20each%20other's%20lives.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20months%2C%20it%20seemed%20like%20every%20woman%20on%20the%20internet%20was%20discussing%20whether%20women%20who%20have%20children%20and%20those%20who%20don't%20can%20remain%20friends%20after%20babies%20come%20along.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20single%20and%20child-free%2C%20and%20I'm%20closer%20than%20ever%20with%20four%20friends%20who%20are%20all%20married%20with%20kids%20%E2%80%94%20all%20thanks%20to%20an%20app.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20joined%20Marco%20Polo%20with%204%20of%20my%20closest%20friends%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAround%20the%20start%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20four%20of%20my%20former%20sorority%20sisters%20and%20I%20joined%20a%20video%20group%20chat%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.marcopolo.me%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EMarco%20Polo%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20app%20that%20allows%20you%20to%20leave%20video%20messages%20and%20watch%20them%20at%20your%20leisure.%20After%20we%20graduated%20from%20the%20University%20of%20San%20Diego%20in%202010%2C%20we%20all%20kept%20tabs%20on%20each%20other%2C%20and%20I%20even%20attended%20two%20of%20their%20weddings.%20But%20I%20didn't%20know%20many%20details%20about%20their%20day-to-day%20lives%20and%20growing%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20all%20changed%20over%20the%20next%20year.%20We%20started%20leaving%20each%20other%20almost%20daily%20video%20messages%20with%20updates%20on%20everything%20from%20the%20mundane%20(chores%2C%20gossip%2C%20complaints%20about%20bad%20customer%20service)%20to%20the%20critical%20(marital%20rifts%2C%20cancer%20diagnoses%2C%20family%20deaths).%20We%20loved%20the%20app%20so%20much%20that%20we%20upgraded%20to%20the%20paid%20version%20%E2%80%94%20%24120%20split%20six%20ways%20%E2%80%94%20so%20we%20can%20watch%20videos%20at%20faster%20speeds%20and%20take%20notes%20along%20the%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20mattered%20that%20we%20saw%20each%20other's%20faces%20so%20much%20%E2%80%94%20seeing%20the%20smiles%2C%20furrowed%20brows%2C%20and%20tears%20strengthened%20our%20connection%20across%20thousands%20of%20miles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20got%20to%20see%20what%20life%20with%20kids%20was%20like%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20time%20I%20moved%20to%20New%20York%20City%20at%2023%20to%20when%20I%20left%20nine%20years%20later%2C%20in%202020%2C%20I%20had%20one%20married%20friend%20and%20zero%20friends%20with%20kids.%20Meanwhile%2C%20my%20Marco%20Polo%20friends%20in%20California%20all%20got%20married%20and%20had%20kids%20by%20their%20mid-20s%3B%20they%20now%20have%2010%20children%20among%20them.%20My%2020s%20centered%20around%20my%20exciting%20media%20career%2C%20dating%20adventures%2C%20and%20late%20nights%20out%20in%20Manhattan.%20These%20women%20also%20had%20full-time%20careers%2C%20but%20their%20lives%20outside%20the%20nine-to-five%20revolved%20around%20sleep%20training%2C%20finding%20the%20right%20day%20care%2C%20discovering%20their%20new%20identities%20as%20mothers%2C%20and%20keeping%20their%20marriages%20intact%20along%20the%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThrough%20Marco%20Polo%2C%20I%20got%20a%20long-distance%20yet%20close-up%20look%20at%20their%20lives.%20They%20never%20sugarcoated%20the%20fact%20that%20parenting%20upends%20most%20aspects%20of%20your%20life%2C%20and%20it's%20often%20grueling%20work.%20They%20struggled%20with%20how%20best%20to%20handle%20their%20kids'%20behavioral%20problems%2C%20from%20anxiety%20to%20aggressiveness%2C%20and%20tried%20to%20learn%20how%20to%20manage%20completely%20irrational%20beings%20with%20empathy%20and%20patience.%20They%20were%20seldom%20well-rested%2C%20and%20they%20talked%20about%20poop%20nonstop.%20And%20there%20was%20a%20new%20emotion%20that%20hovered%20over%20them%20at%20all%20times%3A%20mom%20guilt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20heard%20about%20their%20children%20being%20rushed%20to%20urgent%20care%20for%20ear%20infections%2C%20shortness%20of%20breath%2C%20and%20broken%20legs%2C%20and%20I%20saw%20countless%20anxious%20tears%20shed.%20There%20were%20many%20moments%20of%20awe-inspiring%20love%20and%20tenderness%2C%20too.%20I%20got%20to%20experience%20my%20friend's%20entire%20third%20pregnancy%20and%20then%20witness%20her%20newborn%20son%20grow.%20Sweet%20kids'%20faces%2C%20growing%20and%20changing%20from%20month%20to%20month%2C%20popped%20up%20on%20Marco%20Polo%2C%20cuddling%2C%20giggling%2C%20telling%20me%20about%20their%20day%2C%20begging%20to%20press%20the%20button%20to%20stop%20the%20video.%20One%20day%2C%20the%20moms%20shared%20the%20plethora%20of%20artwork%20their%20kids%20had%20recently%20created%2C%20and%20I%20couldn't%20stop%20smiling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20also%20got%20to%20see%20what%20being%20married%20can%20be%20like%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20friends%20have%20all%20been%20married%20between%20six%20and%2010%20years%20already%2C%20and%20it's%20been%20fascinating%20to%20learn%20about%20the%20intimate%20details%20of%20what%20being%20married%20is%20actually%20like%20%E2%80%94%20I've%20never%20even%20lived%20with%20a%20boyfriend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey've%20talked%20about%20imbalanced%20gender%20roles%20and%20dads%20abandoning%20their%20fair%20share%20of%20the%20physical%20or%20emotional%20labor%20of%20parenthood%2C%20but%20also%20of%20husbands%20taking%20over%20full%20kitchen%20duties%2C%20planning%20date%20nights%2C%20and%20making%20real%20changes%20to%20be%20better%20partners.%20These%20men%20read%20parenting%20books%2C%20gave%20their%20wives%20real%20time%20to%20rest%2C%20and%20even%20decided%20to%20go%20to%20therapy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20top%20of%20everything%20my%20friends%20do%20at%20home%2C%20they've%20all%20got%20coworkers%20and%20bosses%20who%20make%20daily%20demands%20on%20their%20time%20and%20energy%20as%20well.%20We've%20had%20deep%20discussions%20about%20work-life%20balance%2C%20asking%20for%20a%20raise%2C%20and%20being%20a%20female%20breadwinner.%20They%20still%20care%20deeply%20about%20their%20careers%2C%20their%20physical%20and%20mental%20health%2C%20and%20nurturing%20their%20own%20creativity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20don't%20want%20kids%20or%20to%20be%20married%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAround%20the%20time%20I%20turned%2030%2C%20I%20felt%20an%20increasing%20weight%20on%20my%20shoulders%20to%20%3Cem%3Eknow%20for%20sure%3C%2Fem%3E%20whether%20or%20not%20I%20wanted%20kids.%20But%20now%2C%20single%20at%2035%2C%20I'm%20much%20more%20comfortable%20with%20the%20fact%20that%20marriage%20and%20kids%20are%20not%20a%20priority%20for%20me.%20My%20life%20will%