ew%20months%20before%20the%20dates%20on%20which%20elections%20to%20the%20parliament%20and%20several%20States%20are%20scheduled%20to%20be%20held%2C%E2%80%9D%20read%20the%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20present%20incumbents%20of%20the%20office%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(ECI)%20are%20appointees%20of%20the%20political%20executive%20and%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20in%20their%20order%20of%20March%202%2C%202023%20%5BWP(Civil)%20No.104%2F2015%5D%20directed%20the%20government%20to%20consider%20introducing%20a%20more%20transparent%20system%20of%20their%20appointment.%20It%20is%2C%20therefore%2C%20imperative%20that%20the%20government%2C%20with%20the%20approval%20of%20the%20parliament%2C%20puts%20in%20place%20at%20the%20earliest%20a%20transparent%20selection%20process%20for%20the%20ECI%20members%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20this%20to%20be%20possible%2C%20the%20government%20ought%20to%20have%20drafted%20a%20Bill%20in%20line%20with%20the%20norms%20proposed%20by%20the%20apex%20court.%20The%20Bill%20presently%20introduced%20in%20the%20Parliament%20runs%20counter%20to%20the%20apex%20court%E2%80%99s%20suggestions%20and%20it%20negates%20the%20very%20idea%20of%20having%20a%20Commission%20that%20can%20function%20as%20an%20apolitical%2C%20independent%20body%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20August%2010%2C%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20introduced%20this%20Bill%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20objective%20is%20to%20replace%20the%20present%20arbitrary%20system%20of%20appointment%20of%20election%20commissioners%2C%20which%20is%20based%20on%20the%20executive%20considering%20a%20panel%20of%20candidates%20and%20selecting%20one%20considered%20acceptable%20from%20its%20point%20of%20view%20for%20approval%20by%20the%20President%20through%20a%20collegium%20method.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Felection-commissioners-appointment-bill-farewell-to-free-and-fair-elections%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Section%207%20of%20the%20Bill%20seeks%20to%20set%20up%20a%20selection%20committee%20headed%20by%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20which%20will%20have%20one%20Union%20minister%2C%20nominated%20by%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20and%20the%20Leader%20of%20the%20Opposition%20(LoP)%20as%20its%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENeither%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20nor%20any%20eminent%20jurist%20will%20find%20a%20place%20in%20this%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20raises%20concerns%20over%20the%20process%20in%20which%20the%20chief%20election%20commissioner%20(CEC)%20and%20other%20election%20commissioners%20(ECs)%20would%20be%20selected%20by%20the%20political%20executive%20belonging%20to%20the%20ruling%20party%20with%20the%20LoP%20either%20ignored%20or%20overruled.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Felection-commissioners-appointment-bill-farewell-to-free-and-fair-elections%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Section%2010%20of%20the%20Bill%20downgrades%20the%20CEC%20and%20EC%E2%80%99s%20status%20to%20that%20of%20the%20Cabinet%20secretary%20from%20the%20level%20of%20the%20judge%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20as%20being%20treated%20now%20under%20Article%20324(5)%20of%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EM.G.%20Devasahayam%2C%20a%20former%20Army%20and%20IAS%20officer%20and%20coordinator%20of%20the%20Citizen%E2%80%99s%20Commission%20on%20Elections%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Felection-commissioners-appointment-bill-farewell-to-free-and-fair-elections%5C%22%3Easked%3C%2Fa%3E%20whether%20this%20pave%20the%20way%20for%20the%20ECI%20to%20become%20an%20executive%20authority%20instead%20of%20a%20constitutional%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20other%20discussions%2C%20this%20Bill%20is%20on%20the%20agenda%20at%20the%20Winter%20Session%20of%20the%20parliament%2C%20which%20started%20on%20December%204%20and%20will%20run%20till%20December%2022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EReproduced%20below%20is%20the%20full%20statement%2C%20along%20with%20the%20names%20of%20all%20signatories.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cu%3EAppeal%20to%20Members%20of%20the%20Parliament%20to%20align%20the%20Bill%20fully%20with%20the%20norms%20prescribed%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20understand%20that%20the%20government%20has%20reintroduced%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20Other%20Election%20Commissioners%20(Appointment%2C%20Conditions%20of%20Service%20and%20Term%20of%20Office)%20Bill%2C%202023.%20The%20Bill%20is%20likely%20to%20come%20up%20for%20a%20discussion%20at%20the%20winter%20session%20of%20the%C2%A0Parliament%C2%A0to%20be%20convened%20shortly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsidering%20past%20experience%2C%20the%20Bill%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20passed%20by%20the%20Parliament%20with%20little%20discussion.%20If%20enacted%2C%20the%20proposed%20legislation%20in%20its%20present%20form%20will%20cut%20at%20the%20very%20root%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20democracy%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20one-party%20rule%2C%20which%20the%20framers%20of%20the%20Constitution%20would%20never%20have%C2%A0visualised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20urgency%20underlying%20this%20appeal%20arises%20from%20reports%20that%20one%20of%20the%20incumbents%20of%20the%20office%20of%20the%20Commission%2C%20Shri%20Anup%20Chandra%20Pandey%20will%20retire%20in%20February%202024%20and%20if%20the%20Bill%20gets%20enacted%20in%20its%20existing%20form%2C%20the%20process%20of%20appointment%20of%20his%20successor%20will%20become%20completely%20non-transparent%2C%20making%20it%20possible%20for%20the%20NDA%20government%20to%20have%20a%20candidate%20exclusively%20of%20its%20choice%20appointed%20a%20few%20months%20before%20the%20dates%20on%20which%20elections%20to%20the%20Parliament%20and%20several%20States%20are%20scheduled%20to%20be%20held.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20has%20a%20pivotal%20role%20to%20play%20in%20maintaining%20India%20as%20a%20true%20democracy.%20As%20such%2C%20not%20only%20the%20Union%20but%20also%20the%20States%2C%20all%20political%20parties%20and%20in%20particular%20the%20people%20at%20large%20have%20a%20direct%20stake%20in%20its%20being%20a%20vibrant%20and%20reliable%20instrument%20for%20promoting%20democracy.%20The%20fact%20that%20the%20NDA%20government%20has%20rushed%20through%20with%20the%20Bill%20without%20holding%20any%20consultation%20with%20the%20political%20parties%2C%20both%20national%20and%20regional%2C%20without%20consulting%20the%20States%20and%20without%20a%20wider%20public%20discussion%20and%20debate%2C%20displays%20its%20scanty%20respect%20for%20the%20spirit%20of%20federalism%20and%20its%20insensitivity%20to%20the%20democratic%20values%20that%20lie%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20our%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20present%20incumbents%20of%20the%20office%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(ECI)%20are%20appointees%20of%20the%20political%20executive%20and%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20in%20their%20order%20of%20March%202%2C%202023%20%5BWP(Civil)%20No.104%2F2015%5D%20directed%C2%A0the%20government%20to%20consider%20introducing%20a%20more%20transparent%20system%20of%20their%20appointment.%20It%20is%20therefore%20imperative%20that%20the%20government%2C%20with%20the%20approval%20of%20the%20Parliament%2C%20puts%20in%20place%20at%20the%20earliest%20a%20transparent%20selection%20process%20for%20the%20ECI%20members.%20For%20this%20to%20be%20possible%2C%20the%20government%20ought%20to%20have%20drafted%20a%20Bill%20in%20line%20with%20the%20norms%20proposed%20by%20the%20apex%20court.%20The%20Bill%20presently%20introduced%20in%20the%20Parliament%20runs%20counter%20to%20the%20apex%20court%E2%80%99s%20suggestions%20and%20it%20negates%20the%20very%20idea%20of%20having%20a%20Commission%20that%20can%20function%20as%20an%20apolitical%2C%20independent%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArticle%20324%20of%20the%20Constitution%20under%20which%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(ECI)%20is%20set%20up%20and%20the%20laws%20enacted%20thereunder%20envisage%20the%20Commission%20to%20act%20as%20an%20apolitical%20authority%20to%20be%20able%20to%20conduct%20elections%20in%20a%20free%20and%20fair%20manner.%20Many%20provisions%20of%20the%20latest%20Bill%20negate%20that%20concept%2C%20rendering%20the%20Commission%20subservient%20to%20the%20political%20executive%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20the%20other%20political%20parties%2C%20which%20in%20the%20long%20run%20will%20erode%20the%20public%20trust%20in%20it%20and%20dilute%20its%20credibility%2C%20a%20situation%20that%20will%20not%20augur%20well%20for%20the%20nation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20June%2015%2C%201949%2C%20when%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20discussed%20the%20provisions%20included%20in%20the%20draft%20of%20the%20Constitution%20for%20setting%20up%20an%20independent%20Election%20Commission%2C%20Dr%20B%20R%20Ambedkar%20explained%20the%20background%20of%20the%20draft%20provision%20as%20it%20stood%20at%20that%20time%20as%20follows%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Ein%20a%20very%20early%20stage%20in%20the%20proceedings%20of%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%2C%20a%20Committee%20was%20appointed%20to%20deal%20with%20what%20are%20called%20Fundamental%20Rights.%20That%20Committee%20made%20a%20report%20that%20it%20should%20be%20recognised%20that%20the%20independence%20of%20the%20elections%20and%20the%20avoidance%20of%20any%20interference%20by%20the%20executive%20in%20the%20elections%20to%20the%20Legislature%20should%20be%20regarded%20as%20a%20fundamental%20right%20and%20provided%20for%20in%20the%20chapter%20dealing%20with%20Fundamental%20Rights.%20When%20the%20matter%20came%20up%20before%20the%20House%2C%20it%20was%20the%20wish%20of%20the%20House%20that%20while%20there%20was%20no%20objection%20to%20regard%20this%20matter%20as%20of%20fundamental%20importance%2C%20it%20should%20be%20provided%20for%20in%20some%20other%20part%20of%20the%20Constitution%20and%20not%20in%20the%20Chapter%20dealing%20with%20Fundamental%20Rights.%20But%20the%20House%20affirmed%20without%20any%20kind%20of%20dissent%20that%20in%20the%20interests%20of%20purity%20and%20freedom%20of%20elections%20to%20the%20legislative%20bodies%2C%20it%20was%20of%20the%20utmost%20importance%20that%20they%20should%20be%20freed%20from%20any%20kind%20of%20interference%20from%20the%20executive%20of%20the%20day.%20In%20pursuance%20of%20the%20decision%20of%20the%20House%2C%20the%20Drafting%20Committee%20removed%20this%20question%20from%20the%20category%20of%20Fundamental%20Rights%20and%20put%20it%20in%20a%20separate%20part%20containing%20articles%20289%2C%20290%20and%20so%20on.%20Therefore%2C%20so%20far%20as%20the%20fundamental%20question%20is%20concerned%20that%20the%20election%20machinery%20should%20be%20outside%20the%20control%20of%20the%20executive%20Government%2C%20there%20has%20been%20no%20dispute.%20What%20Article%20289%20does%20is%20to%20carry%20out%20that%20part%20of%20the%20decision%20of%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly.%20It%20transfers%20the%20superintendence%2C%20direction%20and%20control%20of%20the%20preparation%20of%20the%20electoral%20rolls%20and%20of%20all%20elections%20to%20Parliament%20and%20the%20Legislatures%20of%20States%20to%20a%20body%20outside%20the%20executive%20to%20be%20called%20the%20Election%20Commission%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20primary%20intent%20underlying%20the%20provisions%20in%20the%20Constitution%2C%20as%20later%20approved%20by%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%2C%20was%20thus%20based%20on%20the%20fundamental%20premise%20that%20the%20Election%20Commission%20should%20be%20outside%20the%20control%20of%20the%20executive%2C%20as%20any%20element%20of%20influence%20by%20the%20executive%20would%20result%20in%20an%20authority%20that%20would%20fail%20to%20inspire%20sufficient%20confidence%20among%20the%20political%20parties%20and%20the%20public%20in%20the%20impartiality%20of%20the%20Commission%20and%20its%20ability%20to%20hold%20elections%20in%20a%20free%20and%20fair%20manner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20existing%20system%20of%20appointment%20of%20the%20Election%20Commissioners%20is%20based%20on%20the%20Executive%20considering%20a%20panel%20of%20candidates%20and%20selecting%20one%20considered%20acceptable%20from%20its%20point%20of%20view%2C%20for%20approval%20by%20the%20President.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20there%20have%20been%20complaints%20from%20several%20political%20parties%20about%20the%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20independence%20as%20a%20Constitutional%20authority%20and%20its%20effectiveness%20to%20be%20able%20to%C2%A0function%20as%20an%20apolitical%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20Shri%20L%20K%20Advani%2C%20in%20a%20letter%20of%20June%202%2C%202012%2C%20addressed%20to%20the%20then%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20Dr%20Manmohan%20Singh%2C%20questioned%20the%20credibility%20of%20the%20existing%20system%20in%20which%20the%20members%20of%20the%20Commission%20were%20appointed%20by%20the%20President%20solely%20on%20the%20advice%20of%20the%20Prime%20Minister.%20He%20said%20that%20it%20would%20not%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Eevoke%20confidence%20among%20the%20people%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D.%20He%20therefore%20proposed%20that%20the%20committee%20that%20selects%20candidates%20for%20appointment%20to%20the%20Commission%20should%20be%20more%20%E2%80%9Cbroad-based%E2%80%9D%20to%20include%20the%20Leader%20of%20Opposition%20and%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%2C%20among%20others%20as%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20recently%2C%20as%20referred%20earlier%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20directed%20the%20government%20to%20consider%20introducing%20a%20more%20transparent%20system%20of%20appointment%20of%20the%20Election%20Commissioners%20and%20made%20the%20following%20observations%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Ekeeping%20in%20view%20the%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Eimportance%20of%20maintaining%20the%20neutrality%20and%20independence%20of%20the%20office%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%20to%20hold%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%20which%20is%20a%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Esine%20qua%20non%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Efor%20upholding%20the%20democracy%20as%20enshrined%20in%20our%20Constitution%2C%20it%20becomes%20imperative%20to%20shield%20the%20appointment%20of%20Election%20Commissioners%20and%20to%20be%20insulated%20from%20the%20executive%20interference.%20It%20is%20the%20need%20of%20the%20hour%20and%20advisable%2C%20in%20my%20view%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Eto%20extend%20the%20protection%20available%20to%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20under%20the%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Efirst%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Eproviso%20to%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EArticle%20324(5)%20to%20other%20Election%20Commissioners%20as%20well%20until%20any%20law%20is%20being%20framed%20by%20the%20Parliament%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%A6%E2%80%A6%E2%80%A6%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3EUntil%20the%20Parliament%20makes%20a%20law%20in%C2%A0consonance%20with%20Article%20324(2)%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20the%20following%20guidelines%20shall%20be%20in%20effect%3A%20(1)%20We%20declare%20that%20the%20appointment%20of%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20the%20Election%20Commissioners%20shall%20be%20made%20on%20the%20recommendations%20made%20by%20a%20three%20member%20Committee%20comprising%20of%20the%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20Leader%20of%20the%20Opposition%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20in%20case%20no%20Leader%20of%20Opposition%20is%20available%2C%20the%20Leader%20of%20the%20largest%20opposition%20party%20in%C2%A0the%20Lok%20Sabha%20in%20terms%20of%20numerical%20strength%20and%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApparently%2C%20it%20is%20in%20pursuance%20of%20the%20above%20observations%20of%20the%20apex%20court%2C%20that%20the%20government%20has%20introduced%20the%20present%20Bill%20in%20the%20Parliament.%C2%A0However%2C%20its%20provisions%20tend%20to%20run%20counter%20to%20the%20norms%20proposed%20by%20the%20apex%20court%20as%20analysed%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESection%207%20of%20the%20Bill%20seeks%20to%20set%20up%20a%20Selection%20Committee%20headed%20by%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20to%20select%20candidates%20to%20be%20appointed%20as%20Election%20Commissioners.%20While%20the%20proposed%20committee%20includes%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20largest%20party%20in%20opposition%2C%20it%20also%20includes%20a%20Union%20Minister%20to%20be%20nominated%20by%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20as%20its%20third%20member.%20It%20does%20not%20include%20anyone%20else%2C%20including%20either%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India.%20Section%206%20provides%20for%20a%20Search%20Committee%20headed%20by%20the%20Cabinet%20Secretary%20with%20two%20other%20Secretaries%20as%20its%20members.%20The%20Search%20Committee%20would%20consider%20candidates%20eligible%20to%20be%20appointed%20as%20Election%20Commissioners%20and%20recommend%20a%20panel%20of%20five%20such%20candidates%20for%20the%20Selection%20Committee%E2%80%99s%20consideration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20salutary%20provisions%20of%20the%20Bill%20include%20a%20fixed%20term%20for%20each%20Election%20Commissioner%20%5BSection%209(1)%5D%2C%20prohibition%20of%20an%20Election%20Commissioner%20being%20reappointed%20%5BSection%209(2)%5D%20and%20a%20rigorous%20and%20transparent%20procedure%20for%20the%20removal%20of%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%2C%20as%20envisaged%20in%20Article%20324(5)%20of%20the%20Constitution%20%5BSection%2011(2)%5D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20there%20are%20other%20provisions%20that%20cause%20serious%20concerns.%20The%20Bill%20in%20its%20present%20form%20fails%20to%20meet%20the%20requirement%20that%20Dr%20Ambedkar%20had%20specifically%20referred%20to%2C%20namely%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Ethat%20the%20election%20machinery%20should%20be%20outside%20the%20control%20of%20the%20executive%20Government%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%2C%C2%A0as%20explained%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Selection%20Committee%20referred%20to%20in%20the%20Bill%2C%20as%20provided%20in%20Section%207%20is%20dominated%20by%20the%20representatives%20of%20the%20political%20executive%20and%20the%20mere%20presence%20of%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20largest%20party%20in%20opposition%20would%20not%20evidently%20alter%20that%20position%2C%20as%20he%2Fshe%20can%20be%20summarily%20overruled%2C%20being%20out-voted%20two-is-to-one..%20The%20Search%20Committee%20itself%20is%20dominated%20by%20civil%20servants%20who%20are%20under%20the%20administrative%20control%20of%20the%20political%20executive%20and%20the%20procedure%20adopted%20by%20it%20for%20considering%20eligible%20candidates%20to%20be%20included%20in%20the%20panel%20remains%20totally%20non-transparent.%20Section%208(2)%20empowers%20the%20Selection%20Committee%20to%C2%A0%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Econsider%20any%20other%20person%20than%20those%20included%20in%20the%20panel%20by%20the%20Search%20Committee%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0Considering%20that%20Section%205%20provides%20that%20candidates%20for%20appointment%20to%20the%20office%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%20%E2%80%9Cshall%20be%20persons%20of%20integrity%2C%20who%20have%20knowledge%20of%20and%20experience%20in%20management%20and%20conduct%20of%20elections%E2%80%9D%2C%C2%A0the%20term%C2%A0%E2%80%9Cintegrity%E2%80%9D%C2%A0and%20the%20other%20criteria%C2%A0not%20having%20been%20defined%20adequately%2C%20it%20permits%20the%20Selection%20Committee%20to%20override%20the%20panel%20recommended%20by%20the%20Search%20Committee%20and%20select%20any%20other%20candidate%20of%20its%20choice.%20The%20leader%20of%20the%20largest%20party%20in%20opposition%2C%20as%20its%20member%2C%20would%20not%20have%20enough%20access%20to%20the%20background%20information%20on%20the%20candidates%20and%2C%20in%20any%20case%2C%20can%20be%20overruled%20by%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20members%20who%20are%20a%20part%20of%20the%20political%20executive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20procedure%20prescribed%20in%20the%20Bill%20for%20removal%20of%20the%20incumbent%20of%20the%20office%20of%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%2C%20as%20provided%20in%20Section%2011(2)%20of%20the%20Bill%2C%20is%20no%20doubt%20rigorous%20enough%2C%20as%20provided%20in%20Article%20324(5)%2C%20that%20Article%20itself%20does%20not%20explicitly%20lay%20down%20a%20similar%20procedure%20for%20removing%20the%20other%20Election%20Commissioners.%20From%20the%20point%20of%20view%20of%20ensuring%20the%20independence%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%2C%20though%20not%20explicitly%20stated%2C%20the%20intention%20underlying%20Article%20324(5)%20should%20be%20deemed%20to%20provide%20a%20similar%20procedure%20being%20adopted%20for%20the%20removal%20of%20the%20other%20Election%20Commissioners.%20Against%20the%20background%20of%20the%20discussions%20in%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20and%20the%20overarching%20objective%20of%20ensuring%20the%20independence%20of%20the%20Commission%2C%20the%20Bill%20ought%20to%20have%20explicitly%20extended%20a%20similar%20procedure%20of%20removal%20of%20the%20other%20Election%20Commissioners.%20This%20assumes%20utmost%20importance%20in%20view%20of%20the%20provision%20in%20Section%2017(2)%20which%20states%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Eif%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20other%20Election%20Commissioners%20differ%20in%20opinion%20on%20any%20matter%2C%20such%20matter%20shall%20be%20decided%20according%20to%20the%20opinion%20of%20the%20majority%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E.%C2%A0Considering%20that%20the%20other%20Election%20Commissioners%20can%20be%20removed%20at%20the%20pleasure%20of%20the%20political%20executive%2C%20the%20mere%20fact%20that%20the%20procedure%20for%20removing%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20is%20rigorous%20does%20not%20confer%20sufficient%20autonomy%20on%20the%20Commission%20as%20a%20whole.%20Since%20the%20procedure%20of%20appointment%20of%20an%20Election%20Commissioner%20in%20the%20first%20instance%20is%20such%20that%20the%20political%20executive%20has%20an%20overriding%20role%20in%20it%20and%20since%20the%20appointment%20itself%20constitutes%20a%20post-retirement%20benefit%20conferred%20on%20selected%20candidates%2C%20the%20independence%20of%20the%20Commission%20as%20a%20whole%2C%20stands%20compromised.%20In%20view%20of%20this%2C%20if%20the%20Bill%20is%20enacted%20in%20its%20present%20form%2C%20the%20other%20political%20parties%20and%20the%20public%20will%20perceive%20the%20Commission%20to%20be%20subservient%20to%20the%20political%20executive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20Article%20324(5)%20of%20the%20Constitution%20indirectly%20treats%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%E2%80%99s%20status%20as%20equivalent%20to%20that%20of%20a%20judge%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20Section%2010%20of%20the%20Bill%20downgrades%20his%2F%20her%20status%20and%20that%20of%20the%20other%20Commissioners%20to%20that%20of%20the%20Cabinet%20Secretary.%20This%20provision%20indirectly%20diminishes%20the%20stature%20of%20the%20Commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20sum%20up%2C%20the%20Bill%20in%20its%20present%20form%20does%20not%20do%20sufficient%20justice%20to%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%E2%80%99s%20vision%20that%20the%C2%A0%E2%80%9Celection%20machinery%20should%20be%20outside%20the%20control%20of%20the%20executive%20Government%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0An%20Election%20Commission%20that%20is%20pliant%20to%20the%20political%20executive%20will%20erode%20the%20credibility%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20order%20to%20uphold%20the%20integrity%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%2C%20the%20following%20legislative%20measures%20need%20to%20be%20considered.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESection%207%20of%20the%20Bill%20should%20be%20modified%20to%20enlarge%20the%20composition%20of%20the%20Selection%20Committee%20to%20include%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20(CJI)%20as%20one%20of%20its%20members%2C%20as%20suggested%20by%20the%20apex%20court.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20status%20of%20a%20member%20of%20the%20ECI%20should%20be%20elevated%20to%20that%20of%20a%20judge%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20Section%2010%20of%20the%20Bill%20should%20be%20appropriately%20amended.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20procedure%20for%20the%20removal%20of%20the%20Election%20Commissioners%20should%20be%20similar%20to%20that%20for%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%2C%20that%20is%2C%20that%20applicable%20to%20a%20Judge%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20This%20needs%20to%20be%20explicitly%20stated%20in%20Section%2011(2).%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EConsidering%20that%20the%20Search%20Committee%2C%20as%20provided%20in%20Section%206%2C%20consists%20exclusively%20of%20Secretaries%20to%20the%20Government%20who%20are%20under%20the%20administrative%20control%20of%20the%20political%20executive%2C%20in%20order%20to%20render%20the%20search%20process%20more%20transparent%2C%20the%20details%20of%20the%20candidates%20considered%20by%20the%20Search%20Committee%20for%20inclusion%20in%20the%20panel%20and%20the%20eligibility%20criteria%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20which%20their%20candidature%20was%20taken%20into%20account%20should%20be%20placed%20before%20the%20Selection%20Committee%20and%20also%20in%20the%20public%20domain%20for%20the%20political%20parties%20and%20the%20public%20to%20see.%20Section%206%20needs%20to%20be%20amended%20to%20take%20this%20into%20account.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESection%208(2)%20which%20empowers%20the%20Selection%20Committee%20to%20consider%20persons%20other%20than%20those%20included%20in%20the%20panel%20should%20be%20suitably%20amended%20to%20require%20the%20Selection%20Committee%20to%20spell%20out%20the%20grounds%20for%20considering%20such%20persons.%20Section%208(2)%20should%20be%20further%20amended%20to%20require%20the%20proceedings%20of%20the%20Selection%20Committee%20to%20be%20placed%20in%20the%20public%20domain.%20The%20proceedings%20should%20specifically%20reflect%20the%20dissenting%20views%20of%20individual%20members%2C%20if%20any.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESection%2017(2)%20should%20be%20amended%20to%20require%20the%20ECI%20to%20place%20in%20the%20public%20domain%20the%20proceedings%20of%20the%20decisions%20taken%2C%20including%20the%20dissenting%20views%20of%20individual%20members%2C%20if%20any.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20appeal%20to%20ALL%20the%20Members%20of%20Parliament%2C%20irrespective%20of%20the%20parties%20to%20which%20they%20belong%2C%20to%20consider%20the%20above%20concerns%2C%20keeping%20in%20view%20the%20long-term%20well-being%20and%20credibility%20of%20our%20democracy%20and%20make%20sure%20that%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20Bill%20are%20so%20altered%20as%20to%20make%20the%20Election%20Commission%20a%20genuinely%20apolitical%20authority%2C%20totally%20independent%20of%20the%20political%20executive%2C%20capable%20of%20conducting%20elections%20in%20a%20free%20and%20fair%20manner%2C%20eliciting%20the%20trust%20of%20all%20political%20parties%20and%2C%20most%20importantly%2C%20invoking%20the%20trust%20of%20the%20people%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEAS%20Sarma%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20Principal%2C%20Administrative%20Staff%20College%20of%20India%20(Hyderabad)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJagdeep%20S.%20Chhokar%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20Professor%2C%20IIM%2C%20Ahmedabad%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAruna%20Roy%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMazdoor%20Kisan%20Shakti%20Sangathan%20(MKSS)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrabhat%20Patnaik%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProfessor%20Emeritus%2C%20JNU%20New%20Delhi%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ES%20P%20Shukla%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20Member%20of%20Planning%20Commission%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuhas%20Borker%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMediaperson%2C%20Broadcaster%2C%20Documentary%20Filmmaker%