ger%20an%20Existential%20Threat%20to%20Linear%20or%20Pay-TV%2C%20Says%20Omdia%20Analyst%3A%20%E2%80%98Perversely%2C%20Advertising%20Keeps%20Creeping%20Into%20TV%E2%80%99%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701768849000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2FTony-Gunnarsson.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235821667%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20direct-to-consumer%20SVOD%20model%20which%20is%20undergoing%20uncertain%20times%20was%20the%20subject%20of%20a%20presentation%20by%20Tony%20Gunnarsson%2C%20senior%20principal%20analyst%2C%20OTT%20video%2C%20media%20and%20entertainment%20at%20Omdia.%20Gunnarsson%20was%20speaking%20at%20Singapore%E2%80%99s%20Asia%20TV%20Forum%20and%20Market.%20The%20number%20of%20pay-TV%20subscribers%20remains%20above%20one%20billion%20and%20is%20likely%20to%20remain%20so%20for%20the%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Naman%20Ramachandran%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ftv%2Fasia%2Fsvod-linear-tv-coexist-omdia-analyst-atf-1235821667%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ftv%2Fasia%2Fsvod-linear-tv-coexist-omdia-analyst-atf-1235821667%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ftv%2Fasia%2Fsvod-linear-tv-coexist-omdia-analyst-atf-1235821667%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Navigating%20Deception%3A%20Dissecting%20the%20Implications%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20Guidelines%20on%20'Dark%20Patterns'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F08%2F05165453%2Fe-commerce-3576213_1280.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDark%20patterns%20refer%20to%20deceptive%20user%20interface%20designs%20employed%20by%20online%20services%20such%20as%20websites%20or%20apps%20to%20influence%20users%20to%20make%20decisions%20they%20otherwise%20might%20not.%20These%20misleading%20tactics%20are%20pervasive%2C%20extending%20from%20popular%20news%20websites%20to%20your%20favourite%20food%20delivery%20app.%20Virtually%20every%20online%20service%20incorporates%20some%20form%20of%20deception%20or%20user%20manipulation%20to%20enhance%20their%20profits.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20response%20to%20this%20issue%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Consumer%20Affairs%20(DoCA)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleaseIframePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1955344%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520draft%2520guidelines%2520define%2520dark%2Cimpairing%2520the%2520consumer%2520autonomy%252C%2520decision%5C%22%3Eintroduced%3C%2Fa%3E%20Guidelines%20for%20Prevention%20and%20Regulation%20of%20Dark%20Patterns%20under%20Section%2018%20of%20the%20Consumer%20Protection%20Act%20of%202019.%20Their%20primary%20objective%20is%20to%20curb%20dishonest%20practices%20and%20promote%20transparency%20in%20the%20online%20marketplace.%20This%20marks%20a%20significant%20and%20commendable%20stride%2C%20considering%20that%20the%20Indian%20legal%20framework%20had%20been%20largely%20silent%20on%20the%20matter%20of%20dark%20patterns%20until%20now.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fconsumeraffairs.nic.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Ffile-uploads%2Flatestnews%2FDraft%2520Guidelines%2520for%2520Prevention%2520and%2520Regulation%2520of%2520Dark%2520Patterns%25202023.pdf%5C%22%3Eguidelines%3C%2Fa%3E%20define%20dark%20patterns%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9Cany%20practices%20or%20deceptive%20design%20patterns%20using%20UI%2FUX%20(user%20interface%2Fuser%20experience)%20interactions%20on%20any%20platform%3B%20designed%20to%20mislead%20or%20trick%20users%20to%20do%20something%20they%20originally%20did%20not%20intend%20or%20want%20to%20do%3B%20by%20subverting%20or%20impairing%20the%20consumer%20autonomy%2C%20decision%20making%20or%20choice%3B%20amounting%20to%20misleading%20advertisement%20or%20unfair%20trade%20practice%20or%20violation%20of%20consumer%20rights.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20proposed%20guidelines%20are%20intended%20to%20apply%20to%20a%20broad%20spectrum%20of%20entities%2C%20encompassing%20sellers%2C%20advertisers%2C%20and%20platforms%20systematically%20providing%20goods%20and%20services%20in%20India.%20Notably%2C%20this%20extends%20beyond%20businesses%20physically%20located%20in%20India%2C%20as%20the%20guidelines%20also%20cover%20businesses%20operating%20outside%20India%20that%20target%20Indian%20citizens%20for%20the%20sale%20of%20goods%20or%20services.%20The%20discourse%20surrounding%20dark%20patterns%20is%20intricately%20connected%20to%20user%20autonomy%20within%20India%E2%80%99s%20privacy%20framework.%20The%20use%20of%20dark%20patterns%2C%20leading%20to%20manipulation%20and%20diversion%20of%20attention%2C%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20nullify%20user%20consent%2C%20resulting%20in%20the%20unlawful%20collection%20and%20processing%20of%20personal%20data%20by%20platforms.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20guidelines%20underscore%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20commitment%20to%20safeguarding%20consumer%20privacy%20and%20purchasing%20autonomy%20on%20the%20Internet%20by%20placing%20a%20significant%20focus%20on%20user%20interface%20design.%20This%20initiative%20is%20particularly%20pertinent%20in%20light%20of%20the%20relationship%20between%20dark%20patterns%20and%20user%20consent%20within%20India%E2%80%99s%20privacy%20regime.%20In%20addition%20to%20the%20guidelines%2C%20DoCA%20had%20already%20issued%20%E2%80%9CAdditional%20Influencer%20Guidelines%20for%20Health%20and%20Wellness%20Celebrities%2C%20Influencers%2C%20and%20Virtual%20Influencers.%E2%80%9D%20These%20guidelines%20outline%20specific%20responsibilities%20for%20influencers%2C%20emphasizing%20caution%20when%20making%20claims%20related%20to%20healthcare%20and%20medicine.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20guidelines%20state%20that%20the%20application%20is%20wide-ranging%20and%20thus%20for%20%E2%80%9Call%20platforms%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cadvertisers%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Csellers%E2%80%9D.%20It%20does%20not%20make%20an%20effort%20to%20define%20all%20the%20terms%20and%20makes%20vague%20references%20to%20the%20dark%20patterns%2C%20such%20that%20the%20applicability%20remains%20under%20question.%20However%2C%20the%20definition%20clause%20limits%20the%20meaning%20to%20as%20defined%20under%20the%20Consumer%20Protection%20(E-Commerce)%20Rules%2C%202020.%20In%20addition%20to%20the%20vague%20applicability%20and%20definitions%2C%20the%20penalty%20thresholds%20haven%E2%80%99t%20been%20clearly%20defined%20in%20the%20guidelines.%20There%20are%20no%20precise%20definitions%20of%20infractions%20or%20punishment%20criteria%20in%20the%20guidelines.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20it%20stands%2C%20the%20Consumer%20Protection%20Act%20of%202019%20would%20impose%20severe%20fines%20on%20any%20of%20the%20dark%20patterns%20mentioned%20in%20Annexure%201.%20Non-compliance%20with%20the%20Act%E2%80%99s%20directions%20can%20lead%20to%20imprisonment%20for%20up%20to%20six%20months%2C%20a%20fine%20of%20up%20to%20Rs%2020%20lakh%2C%20or%20both.%20Additionally%2C%20causing%20false%20or%20misleading%20advertisement%20which%20is%20prejudicial%20to%20the%20interest%20of%20consumers%2C%20is%20also%20a%20punishable%20offence%2C%20with%20imprisonment%20of%20up%20to%20two%20years%20and%20a%20fine%20of%20up%20to%20Rs%2010%20lakh.%20The%20imprisonment%20and%20fine%20increases%20for%20subsequent%20offences.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELegislation%20such%20as%20the%20Information%20Technology%20(Reasonable%20Security%20Practices%20and%20Procedures%20and%20Sensitive%20Personal%20Data%20or%20Information)%20Rules%2C%202011%20(%E2%80%9CSPDI%20Rules%E2%80%9D)%20mandates%20the%20informed%20consent%20of%20users%20before%20collecting%20their%20sensitive%20personal%20data.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20newly%20enacted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fwill-the-data-protection-law-empower-the-public%5C%22%3EDigital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%202023%20places%20importance%20on%20obtaining%20explicit%20consent%20from%20the%20Data%20Principal%20before%20processing%20such%20data.%20Implicit%20or%20opt-out%20consent%2C%20lacking%20a%20clear%2C%20positive%2C%20and%20affirmative%20action%2C%20is%20not%20considered%20valid%20under%20these%20regulations.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20global%20trend%20towards%20prioritising%20users%E2%80%99%20free%20and%20informed%20consent%20is%20evident%20in%20data%20protection%20laws%20worldwide.%20Various%20jurisdictions%2C%20including%20the%20US%20and%20the%20EU%2C%20have%20responded%20to%20the%20risks%20posed%20by%20dark%20patterns%20through%20legislation%20aimed%20at%20protecting%20both%20privacy%20and%20consumer%20rights.%20For%20instance%2C%20in%20the%20US%2C%20the%20California%20Consumer%20Privacy%20Rights%20Act%2C%202020%2C%20and%20the%20California%20Consumer%20Privacy%20Act%2C%202018%2C%20recognise%20dark%20patterns%20and%20discourage%20their%20usage%20by%20rendering%20consent%20obtained%20through%20them%20invalid.%20In%20the%20EU%2C%20legislations%20such%20as%20the%20General%20Data%20Protection%20Act%2C%20the%20Digital%20Services%20Act%2C%20the%20Digital%20Markets%20Act%2C%20and%20the%20Unfair%20Commercial%20Practices%20Directive%20provide%20safeguards%20against%20manipulative%20tactics%20online.%20Notably%2C%20the%20French%20Data%20Protection%20Act%20resulted%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.huntonprivacyblog.com%2F2023%2F01%2F06%2Fcnil-fines-apple-8-million-euros-over-personalized-ads%2F%5C%22%3E%E2%82%AC8%20million%20fine%20on%20Apple%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20implementing%20the%20%E2%80%98personalised%20ads%E2%80%99%20setting%20as%20the%20default%20without%20prior%20consent%20and%20making%20it%20challenging%20to%20change%20the%20setting%20through%20multiple%20steps.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20guidelines%20must%20comprehensively%20address%20the%20myriad%20privacy%20risks%20associated%20with%20dark%20patterns%2C%20particularly%20focusing%20on%20the%20threat%20posed%20by%20the%20unauthorised%20collection%20of%20excessive%20and%20unnecessary%20personal%20data%20without%20the%20informed%20consent%20of%20consumers.%20Even%20with%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Act%2C%202023%2C%20there%20remains%20a%20potential%20gap%20as%20it%20does%20not%20specifically%20govern%20the%20interfaces%20or%20designs%20responsible%20for%20collecting%20personal%20data.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnnexure%201%20of%20the%20guidelines%20serves%20as%20an%20indicative%2C%20though%20not%20exhaustive%2C%20list%20of%20dark%20patterns.%20However%2C%20recognising%20the%20evolving%20nature%20of%20deceptive%20practices%2C%20the%20guidelines%20should%20acknowledge%20the%20possibility%20of%20additional%20dark%20patterns.%20To%20facilitate%20this%2C%20consumers%2C%20civil%20society%2C%20or%20market%20players%20should%20be%20empowered%20to%20report%20new%20instances%20of%20dark%20patterns%20through%20an%20institutionalised%20feedback%20mechanism%20to%20the%20ministry.%20Once%20identified%2C%20the%20responsibility%20for%20limiting%20or%20discontinuing%20the%20deployment%20of%20dark%20patterns%20should%20squarely%20rest%20with%20market%20participants.%20This%20approach%20encourages%20industry%20self-regulation%2C%20with%20necessary%20oversight%20from%20the%20ministry%20and%20valuable%20consumer%20feedback.%20This%20collaborative%20effort%20ensures%20that%20the%20guidelines%20remain%20dynamic%20and%20responsive%20to%20emerging%20challenges%20in%20the%20realm%20of%20online%20consumer%20protection.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EBhuvnesh%20Kumar%20and%20Sharad%20Panwar%20are%20fourth-year%20law%20students%20at%20National%20Law%20University%2C%20Jodhpur.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701768637000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F08%2F05165453%2Fe-commerce-3576213_1280.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Findia-guidelines-dark-patterns-implications%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20guidelines%20must%20comprehensively%20address%20the%20risks%20associated%20with%20dark%20patterns%2C%20particularly%20focusing%20on%20the%20threat%20posed%20by%20the%20collection%20of%20excessive%20and%20unnecessary%20personal%20data%20without%20informed%20consent.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Findia-guidelines-dark-patterns-implications%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Prince%20Harry%20challenges%20UK%20government's%20decision%20to%20strip%20him%20of%20security%20detail%20when%20he%20moved%20to%20US%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701768497000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105752783%2Cimgsize-39226.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fuk%2Fprince-harry-challenges-uk-governments-decision-to-strip-him-of-security-detail-when-he-moved-to-us%2Farticleshow%2F105752783.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F105752783.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EThe%20Duke%20of%20Sussex%20said%20he%20wants%20protection%20when%20he%20visits%20home%20and%20claimed%20it's%20partly%20because%20an%20aggressive%20press%20jeopardizes%20his%20safety%20and%20that%20of%20his%20family.%20The%20three-day%20hearing%20scheduled%20to%20begin%20in%20London's%20High%20Court%20is%20the%20latest%20in%20a%20string%20of%20Harry's%20legal%20cases%20that%20have%20kept%20London%20judges%20busy%20as%20he%20takes%20on%20the%20U.K.%20government%20and%20the%20British%20tabloid%20media.%20It%20was%20not%