6%2C%202023.%20Ahead%20of%20its%20India%20debut%2C%20here%20are%20expected%20visual%20changes%2C%20features%20and%20specs%20of%20the%20Hyundai%20Creta%20facelift.%20Take%20a%20look.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22PRACHI%20AHLUWALIA%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fauto%2Fcars%2Fhyundai-creta-facelift-india-launch-on-january-16-expected-price-features-specs%2Farticleshow%2F105750085.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SC%20Shields%20Journalist%20from%20Arrest%20Over%20Tweets%20on%20Manipur%20Violence%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F12%2Fpress-freedom-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20stayed%20criminal%20proceedings%20against%20independent%20journalist%20Makepeace%20Sitlhou%2C%20after%20she%20made%20critical%20remarks%20on%20Twitter%20against%20the%20Manipur%20government%E2%80%99s%20alleged%20failure%20to%20control%20the%20spiraling%20violence%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20was%20named%20in%20a%20first%20information%20report%20(FIR)%20registered%20at%20Imphal%20(West)%20police%20station%2C%20by%20slapping%20against%20her%20Sections%20120B%20(criminal%20conspiracy)%2C%20153A%20(promoting%20enmity%20between%20two%20groups)%2C%20500%20(defamation)%2C%20and%20505(2)%20(statements%20conducing%20to%20public%20mischief)%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20(IPC).%20The%20FIR%20was%20based%20on%20a%20complaint%20by%20one%20Lairenlakpam%20Sandeep%2C%20a%20resident%20of%20Lamboikhongnangkhong.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20complainant%20alleged%20that%20Sitlhou%20had%20%E2%80%9Cused%20social%20media%20platforms%20as%20a%20tool%20to%20propagate%20misleading%20statements%20and%20to%20destabilise%20a%20democratically%20elected%20government%2C%20disturb%20communal%20harmony%20by%20creating%20enmity%20amongst%20communities%20and%20to%20defame%20the%20state%20government%20and%20one%20particular%20community%E2%80%9D%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Fsupreme-court-stays-criminal-proceedings-against-manipur-journalist-makepeace-sitlhou%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Leaflet%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20went%20on%20to%20allege%20that%20Sitlhou%2C%20through%20her%20tweets%20on%20the%20social%20media%20platform%20X%20(formerly%20known%20as%20Twitter)%2C%20made%20%E2%80%9Cfalse%20statements%20and%20propaganda%E2%80%9D%20with%20the%20purpose%20%E2%80%9Cto%20incite%20one%20particular%20community%2C%20to%20topple%20such%20democratically%20elected%20government%E2%80%9D.%20Her%20statements%2C%20he%20said%2C%20are%20a%20%E2%80%9Cthreat%20to%20the%20security%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESitlhou%2C%20in%20her%20petition%2C%20hit%20out%20at%20the%20arguments%20made%20by%20the%20complainant%20and%20defended%20her%2012%20tweets%20which%20are%20under%20scrutiny.%20Her%20petition%20underlined%20that%20as%20a%20journalist%20she%20tweeted%20against%20rumours%2C%20violence%2C%20and%20the%20lack%20of%20action%20and%20political%20will%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20political%20establishment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20petitioner%20has%20further%20expressed%20her%20opinion%20against%20the%20deeply%20unfortunate%20demands%20for%20certain%20ethnic%20groups%20to%20%E2%80%98go%20back%20where%20they%20belong%E2%80%99%20and%20has%20highlighted%20the%20ethnic%20nature%20of%20the%20violence%20that%20had%20prevailed%20at%20the%20time%20of%20authoring%20the%20tweets%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sithlhou%E2%80%99s%20petition%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20further%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CAny%20incursion%20on%20the%20freedom%20of%20the%20petitioner%20as%20a%20citizen%20and%20a%20journalist%20to%20uncover%20and%20present%20the%20truth%2C%20protected%20by%20Articles%2019%20and%2021%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20would%20have%20a%20chilling%20effect%20on%20journalism%20in%20the%20country.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20bench%20led%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%2C%20and%20comprising%20Justice%20J.B.%20Pardiwala%20and%20Justice%20Manoj%20Misra%2C%20granted%20her%20relief.%C2%A0%E2%80%9CPending%20further%20orders%2C%20there%20shall%20be%20a%20stay%20in%20proceedings%20concerning%20the%20FIRs%20against%20her.%20Issue%20notice.%20Serve%20to%20the%20standing%20counsel%20of%20the%20Manipur%20government%2C%E2%80%9D%20CJI%20dictated%20the%20order%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-grants-interim-relief-to-manipur-journalist-against-firs-over-tweets-on-manipur-violence-243694%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20%3Cem%3ELivelaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Manipur%20government%20is%20facing%20allegations%20of%20filing%20cases%20indiscriminately%20against%20journalists%2C%20who%20are%20reporting%20and%20expressing%20views%20on%20unabated%20ethnic%20violence%20in%20the%20state.%20In%20September%2C%20the%20apex%20court%20granted%20interim%20protection%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fmanipur-police-files-fir-against-editors-guild-fact-finding-team-cites-revoked-sec-66a%5C%22%3Ethree%20journalists%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Editors%20Guild%20of%20India%20from%20coercive%20action%20after%20they%20were%20booked%20by%20Manipur%20Police.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701763530000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F12%2Fpress-freedom-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-stays-criminal-proceedings-against-journalist-booked-for-tweets-on-manipur-violence%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Independent%20journalist%20Makepeace%20Sitlhou%20made%20allegedly%20critical%20remarks%20against%20Manipur%20government's%20failure%20to%20control%20the%20spiraling%20violence%20in%20the%20state.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-stay